		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />- Some games are mute, completly. Castlevania and Metroid don't play a single note, no matter the track number. Gremlins 2 doesn't play the first track, and the other tracks have a small latency to start playing the square waves. Of course this annoyance doesn't occur in the emulated game, so I'm unsure if this is a CPU or an obscure APU bug.

		

